{"v":"1.0.0","d":{"name":"Control.Monad.ST.Uncurried","comments":[{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" | This module defines types for STf uncurried functions, as well as"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" | functions for converting back and forth between them."},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" | The general naming scheme for functions and types in this module is as"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" | follows:"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" | * `STFn{N}` means, an uncurried function which accepts N arguments and"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |   performs some STs. The first N arguments are the actual function's"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |   argument. The last type argument is the return type."},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" | * `runSTFn{N}` takes an `STFn` of N arguments, and converts it into"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |   the normal PureScript form: a curried function which returns an ST"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |   action."},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" | * `mkSTFn{N}` is the inverse of `runSTFn{N}`. It can be useful for"},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |   callbacks."},{"tag":"LineComment","_1":" |"}],"imports":{"tag":"Leaf"},"dataTypes":{"tag":"Leaf"},"bindings":[],"exports":{"tag":"Node","_1":5,"_2":20,"_3":"mkSTFn8","_5":{"tag":"Node","_1":4,"_2":8,"_3":"mkSTFn4","_5":{"tag":"Node","_1":3,"_2":4,"_3":"mkSTFn2","_5":{"tag":"Node","_1":2,"_2":2,"_3":"mkSTFn1","_5":{"tag":"Leaf"},"_6":{"tag":"Node","_1":1,"_2":1,"_3":"mkSTFn10","_5":{"tag":"Leaf"},"_6":{"tag":"Leaf"}}},"_6":{"tag":"Node","_1":1,"_2":1,"_3":"mkSTFn3","_5":{"tag":"Leaf"},"_6":{"tag":"Leaf"}}},"_6":{"tag":"Node","_1":2,"_2":3,"_3":"mkSTFn6","_5":{"tag":"Node","_1":1,"_2":1,"_3":"mkSTFn5","_5":{"tag":"Leaf"},"_6":{"tag":"Leaf"}},"_6":{"tag":"Node","_1":1,"_2":1,"_3":"mkSTFn7","_5":{"tag":"Leaf"},"_6":{"tag":"Leaf"}}}},"_6":{"tag":"Node","_1":4,"_2":11,"_3":"runSTFn3","_5":{"tag":"Node","_1":3,"_2":4,"_3":"runSTFn1","_5":{"tag":"Node","_1":1,"_2":1,"_3":"